V1.1 MS-PC: MERITS AND DEFECTS IN AUTO-REVIEWED AFTER 1 YEAR:
  - The presentation is a bit 'too immediate and monotonous, but 
    still always nice and above all simple, almost to think like
    a mirror the soul of the game, only there is no possibility of
    get out while they're running, and you have to put up with all 
    (except pressing Ctrl-Break and then type SYSTEM);
  - Drafting the entire program makes use of my method
    staff, maybe not innovative, which uses the insertion
    individual statements line by line, with some exceptions:
    the advantage is upstream of program implementation,
    in regard to the fact that if the command interpreter 
    indicates a error, returns the line number of the single 
    instruction, enabling you to debug;
  - Do not prefer the fact that the boot is entrusted to a batch 
    file because it means that over the presentation, the BASIC 
    interpreter to close down and reopen immediately to load the 
    actual game just when you could fix everything with another 
    line only, but unfortunately I realized after I had made!;
  - The installation is quite simple, and has a 'lock' of
    security that is in the fact of having to specify in the file
    DRIVELOC.GWT the path to the directory where the
    file of the game and someone will appreciate this feature, 
    while hate someone, especially those who would copy the entire 
    game in other locations / directories;
  - The winds internships are to be explored, and are organized in
    individual files as regards the loading during the
    game: they are data-file consisting of a few bytes, 
    I consider it a real waste of resources and space;
  - The fact of having to reach its 300 points is almost a
    handicap, since in stage where the screen is full of
    obstacles your track will no longer have space where to stand, 
    but I repeat that this is obviously a further difficulty
    (Otherwise everyone would be able to complete it!);
  - The first bonus is a bit 'suck!: Only 50 points, well,
    contributes, albeit slightly, in the fight for the last point!;
  - The fifth Bonus, which is what clears all obstacles
    fixed (including the old track), can be considered a
    handicap but also because it allows you to remove all
    white ball (your enemy) to leave one last spot,
    making sure that it still remains one fixed obstacle 
    on the screen (?);
  - When you enter your name at the end to know if you are
    achieved the best score, you have to type
    unequivocally ten characters, otherwise the game is
    practically blocked: no comment!;
  - If you complete the twentieth picture is displayed
    final sequence: it too is almost sparse, but what you can
    expect from an arcade game!;
  - The software in general is good: not a problem of instability
    or the operating system takes up very little storage space 
    and is easy installation;
  - The package instructions HelpWare is well made compared
    other software (often much more reserved), especially
    in the instructions;
